This study identified 71 raw materials from 69 plants belonging to 31 families and 65 genera (

  Appendix A
 ). The plant species with the highest UV was 
 Platostoma palustre (Blume) A.J.Paton (72.73%), followed by 
 Bidens pilosa L. (49.09%) and 
 Pteris multifida Poir. (43.64%). The most commonly used plants belonged to the family Compositae (18.84%), followed by the family Lamiaceae (15.94%) (

  Figure 2A
 ). The raw materials were mainly prepared from whole plants (47.89%), followed by stems and twigs (18.31%) (

  Figure 2B
 ). It is worth noting that these plants are a high proportion of native Taiwan species and are grown in Taiwan (

  Figure 3
 ).
